OL,3,CCouncil to pay compensation after
OL,4,Csudden closure of dementia care home
OL,6,FAn independent review into the
OL,7,Fincident which found the closure "was
OL,8,Fnot justified" and described how one
OL,9,Fresident died 16 days after being
OL,10,Fmoved, called for compensation to be
OL,11,Fpaid to residents and their families.
OL,13,FThe report which was published in
OL,14,FAugust 2024 also found the council's
OL,15,Freputation had been "severely damaged".
OL,17,FWakefield Council has confirmed that a
OL,18,Ffinancial settlement has been agreed,
OL,19,Fbut said it would not be publicly
OL,20,Fdisclosing the amounts involved.
